tweet: So what are the lessons we can learn from this nugget of history?  Don’t underestimate the EV revolution. There has never been an economic shift like this — transpiration powers the economy.   Daimler thought they had made good money their investment. They underestimated Tesla.

name: Third Row Tesla Podcast
tweet: Happy ending, right? Well, not so much.   Today Tesla is valued at nearly TWICE as much as Daimler.   If held today, that 9% stake would be worth $8.25 billion, making the original $730 million in profits look like a rounding error.   Tesla sold 112k EVs in Q4. Mercedes? 55!

name: Third Row Tesla Podcast
tweet: In 2009, Tesla was on the verge of bankruptcy. They needed cash bad, or it was lights off.   Guess who decided to save them? Daimler! They bought 9% of Tesla for $50 million.   When they sold their stake for $780 million just five years later, they made $730 million in profits.
